    "attributes": {
        "action": "Extend the Maintenance loan to cover part time distance learning students",
        "additional_details": "The Open University suggests 32 hours of study a week for someone wanting to graduate in 3 years from a standard Bachelors degree. This means they could not work a full time job and study, leaving them with little option for money. This should be changed to allow such students to apply for a maintenance loan as other students are able to.",
        "background": "Many students studying with institutions like the Open University study full time hours meaning they are unable to work a full time job. However they can\u2019t apply for a maintenance loan like other students",
